92
00:05:24,720 --> 00:05:28,720
[ Man Talking,   Indistinct ]

93
00:05:30,720 --> 00:05:35,730
WITH THE SKYROCKETING SALARIES, AND YOU ARE ONE OF THE GUYS RESPONSIBLE.

94
00:05:35,730 --> 00:05:37,730
[ Jesse's Voice ] FUCK YOU.

95
00:05:37,730 --> 00:05:40,230
[ Voices Overlapping ]

96
00:05:40,230 --> 00:05:43,240
[ Jerry Continues ] TWO DAYS LATER AT OUR CORPORATE CONFERENCE IN MIAMI,

97
00:05:43,740 --> 00:05:46,740
A BREAKTHROUGH. [ Man ]  I ALREADY HAD 18 MILLION ON THE TABLE.

98
00:05:47,240 --> 00:05:49,240
BREAKDOWN? BREAKTHROUGH.

99
00:05:49,240 --> 00:05:52,250
[ Boy ] I JUST WANT AN AUTOGRAPH. [ Jesse ]  FUCK YOU.

100
00:05:52,250 --> 00:05:54,750
[ Doctor ] DO YOU KNOW YOUR NAME?

101
00:05:54,750 --> 00:05:58,250
[ Jerry ] I COULDN'T ESCAPE ONE SIMPLE THOUGHT.

102
00:06:00,250 --> 00:06:02,250
I HATED MYSELF.

103
00:06:04,260 --> 00:06:06,760
NO, NO, NO. HERE'S WHAT IT WAS.

104
00:06:06,760 --> 00:06:10,260
I HATED MY PLACE IN THE WORLD.

105
00:06:15,770 --> 00:06:19,270
I HAD SO MUCH TO SAY AND NO ONE TO LISTEN.

106
00:06:19,270 --> 00:06:21,270
[ Typing, Beeps ]

107
00:06:21,270 --> 00:06:24,780
AND THEN IT HAPPENED.

108
00:06:25,780 --> 00:06:29,780
IT WAS THE ODDEST, MOST UNEXPECTED THING.

109
00:06:31,280 --> 00:06:33,790
I BEGAN WRITING WHAT THEY CALL "A MISSION STATEMENT."

110
00:06:33,790 --> 00:06:36,290
NOT A MEMO, A MISSION STATEMENT.

111
00:06:36,290 --> 00:06:39,290
YOU KNOW, A SUGGESTION FOR THE FUTURE OF OUR COMPANY.

112
00:06:40,790 --> 00:06:43,800
A NIGHT LIKE THIS DOESN'T COME ALONG VERY OFTEN.

113
00:06:44,300 --> 00:06:45,800
I SEIZED IT.

114
00:06:47,300 --> 00:06:51,300
WHAT STARTED OUT AS 1 PAGE BECAME 25.

115
00:06:51,300 --> 00:06:54,810
SUDDENLY, I WAS MY FATHER'S SON AGAIN.

116
00:06:54,810 --> 00:06:57,810
I WAS REMEMBERING THE SIMPLE PLEASURES OF THIS JOB--

117
00:06:57,810 --> 00:07:00,310
HOW I ENDED UP HERE OUT OF LAW SCHOOL;

118
00:07:00,310 --> 00:07:03,820
THE WAY A STADIUM SOUNDS WHEN ONE OF MY PLAYERS PERFORMS WELL ON THE FIELD;

119
00:07:03,820 --> 00:07:08,320
THE WAY WE ARE MEANT TO PROTECT THEM IN HEALTH AND IN INJURY.

120
00:07:08,320 --> 00:07:12,820
WITH SO MANY CLIENTS, WE HAD FORGOTTEN WHAT WAS IMPORTANT.

121
00:07:12,820 --> 00:07:15,830
I WROTE AND WROTE AND WROTE AND WROTE,

122
00:07:15,830 --> 00:07:18,330
AND I'M NOT EVEN A WRITER.

123
00:07:18,330 --> 00:07:21,830
I WAS REMEMBERING EVEN THE WORDS OF THE ORIGINAL SPORTS AGENT, MY MENTOR,

124
00:07:21,830 --> 00:07:23,840
THE LATE, GREAT DICKY FOX, WHO SAID--

125
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:27,340
THE KEY TO THIS BUSINESS IS PERSONAL RELATIONSHIPS.

126
00:07:27,840 --> 00:07:29,840
[ Jerry ] SUDDENLY IT WAS ALL PRETTY CLEAR.

127
00:07:29,840 --> 00:07:33,350
THE ANSWER WAS: FEWER CLIENTS.

128
00:07:33,350 --> 00:07:35,850
LESS MONEY. MORE ATTENTION.

129
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:38,850
CARING FOR THEM, CARING FOR OURSELVES AND THE GAMES TOO.

130
00:07:39,350 --> 00:07:41,850
JUST STARTING OUR LIVES, REALLY.

131
00:07:41,850 --> 00:07:46,860
I'LL BE FIRST TO ADMIT IT. WHAT I WAS WRITING WAS SOMEWHAT TOUCHY-FEELY.

132
00:07:46,860 --> 00:07:50,860
I DIDN'T CARE. I HAD LOST THE ABILITY TO BULLSHIT.

133
00:07:50,860 --> 00:07:53,870
IT WAS THE ME I'D ALWAYS WANTED TO BE.

134
00:07:57,370 --> 00:07:59,870
I TOOK IT IN A BAG TO A COPYMAT IN THE MIDDLE OF THE NIGHT...

135
00:07:59,870 --> 00:08:02,380
AND PRINTED UP 110 COPIES.

136
00:08:02,380 --> 00:08:04,880
EVEN THE COVER LOOKED LIKE THE CATCHER IN THE RYE.

137
00:08:04,880 --> 00:08:08,880
I ENTITLED IT, THE THINGS WE THINK AND DO NOT SAY:

138
00:08:10,380 --> 00:08:12,880
THE FUTURE OF OUR BUSINESS.

139
00:08:12,880 --> 00:08:16,390
THAT'S HOW YOU BECOME GREAT, MAN.

140
00:08:16,890 --> 00:08:19,390
HANG YOUR BALLS OUT THERE.

141
00:08:19,390 --> 00:08:21,390
THANKS.

142
00:08:22,390 --> 00:08:24,900
EVERYBODY GOT A COPY.

143
00:08:24,900 --> 00:08:27,400
THERE ARE DANGEROUS ANIMALS IN THE WORLD. SOME WALK ON TWO FEET.

144
00:08:27,900 --> 00:08:29,900
THEY DON'T WANT PEACE. THEY'RE NOT CAPABLE OF LOVE.

145
00:08:29,900 --> 00:08:35,410
SOCIETY-- AND THAT MEANS YOU AND YOU-- NEED PROTECTION FROM THESE WARPED MINDS.

146
00:08:35,410 --> 00:08:38,410
???? [ TV ]

147
00:08:50,420 --> 00:08:52,420
BOOM.

148
00:08:54,430 --> 00:08:57,930
HI, THIS IS JERRY MAGUIRE. DID THOSE MANUSCRIPTS GET--

149
00:08:57,930 --> 00:08:59,930
